timeline.bodyText:
org.checkerframework.javacutil.trees.TreeBuilder#buildLiteral seems to build a literal tree from a given value.
You should be able to do something like this:
    public static LiteralTree buildLiteral(Object value, ProcessingEnvironment env) {
        Context context = ((JavacProcessingEnvironment) env).getContext();
         TreeMaker maker = TreeMaker.instance(context);
        return maker.Literal(value);
    }

(This sort of method should be in TreeUtils.)
In case it's not easy to figure out.  Here are the imports for the code above:
